text: Othmar Bach (born September 14, 1914) is a Swiss canoeist who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics. In 1936 he and his partner Werner Zimmermann finished sixth in the K-2 10000 metres competition. ==References== *Othmar Bach's profile at Sports Reference.com Category:1914 births Category:Canoeists at the 1936 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic canoeists of Switzerland Category:Possibly living people Category:Swiss male canoeists
